  "prompt": "Does Microsoft own Google?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, **Microsoft does not own Google**. Both Microsoft and Google are major, independent multinational technology companies, each with its own range of products and services.\n\n- **Google** is a subsidiary of **Alphabet Inc.**, which was created in 2015 as Google's parent company. Alphabet oversees various other businesses and ventures apart from Google, including areas like self-driving cars (Waymo), life sciences (Verily), and more.\n\n- **Microsoft**, on the other hand, is an independent company known for products like Windows, Office Suite, Azure (its cloud platform), and the Surface line of devices. Microsoft and Google often compete in several sectors, including cloud computing, productivity software, and search engines.\n\nWhile both companies collaborate and compete in different domains, there is no ownership relationship between Microsoft and Google. Each operates separately under their respective corporate structures.",
